The Telegraph - Calcutta
 ICC steps on doping
London: In a bid to stop the doping menace from spreading to cricket, the ICC announced strict measures on Monday, which included a two-year ban on players or officials who breach its anti-doping policy during the next months Champions Trophy. The ICC was planning to use World Anti-Doping Agency (Wada) accredited laboratories for testing the samples collected during all the 15 matches of the competition, revealed ICC chief executive Malcolm Speed. (PTI)  Copyright 
